{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52b556db-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1611"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1611"},"text":"§ 1611.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Certain types of property immune from execution","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id52b556dc-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1611/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Notwithstanding the provisions of section 1610 of this chapter, the property of those organizations designated by the President as being entitled to enjoy the privileges, exemptions, and immunities provided by the International Organizations Immunities Act shall not be subject to attachment or any other judicial process impeding the disbursement of funds to, or on the order of, a foreign state as the result of an action brought in the courts of the United States or of the States.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id52b556dd-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1611/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" Notwithstanding the provisions of section 1610 of this chapter, the property of a foreign state shall be immune from attachment and from execution, if—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id52b556de-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1611/b/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the property is that of a foreign central bank or monetary authority held for its own account, unless such bank or authority, or its parent foreign government, has explicitly waived its immunity from attachment in aid of execution, or from execution, notwithstanding any withdrawal of the waiver which the bank, authority or government may purport to effect except in accordance with the terms of the waiver; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id52b556df-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1611/b/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":" the property is, or is intended to be, used in connection with a military activity and","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id52b556e0-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1611/b/2/A"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"A"},"text":"(A)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is of a military character, or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subparagraph","attrib":{"id":"id52b556e1-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1611/b/2/B"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"B"},"text":"(B)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" is under the control of a military authority or defense agency.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id52b556e2-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s1611/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Notwithstanding the provisions of section 1610 of this chapter, the property of a foreign state shall be immune from attachment and from execution in an action brought under section 302 of the Cuban Liberty and Democratic Solidarity (LIBERTAD) Act of 1996 to the extent that the property is a facility or installation used by an accredited diplomatic mission for official purposes.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52b556e3-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/583/s4/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–583, § 4(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2897"},"text":"90 Stat. 2897","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/114/tIII/s302/e"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–114, title III, § 302(e)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-03-12"},"text":"Mar. 12, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/818"},"text":"110 Stat. 818","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52b556e4-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id52b556e5-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id52b556e6-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The International Organizations Immunities Act, referred to in subsec. (a), is title I of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1945-12-29/ch652"},"text":"act Dec. 29, 1945, ch. 652","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/59/669"},"text":"59 Stat. 669","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to subchapter XVIII (§ 288 et seq.) of chapter 7 of Title 22, Foreign Relations and Intercourse. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s288"},"text":"section 288 of Title 22","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 302 of the Cuban Liberty and Democratic Solidarity (LIBERTAD) Act of 1996, referred to in subsec. (c), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/114/s302"},"text":"section 302 of Pub. L. 104–114","children":[],"tail":", which amended this section and enacted "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6082"},"text":"section 6082 of Title 22","children":[],"tail":", Foreign Relations and Intercourse."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id52b556e7-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/114"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–114","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (c)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id52b556e8-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id52b556e9-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1996 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/114"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–114","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-08-01"},"text":"Aug. 1, 1996","children":[],"tail":", or date determined pursuant to suspension authority of President under section 6085(b) or (c) of Title 22, Foreign Relations and Intercourse, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t22/s6085"},"text":"section 6085 of Title 22","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"id52b556ea-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective 90 days after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/583/s8"},"text":"section 8 of Pub. L. 94–583","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s1602"},"text":"section 1602 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
